The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Business Briefs
                                                                                                               Business Briefs
                              
	 New Delhi, Sept. 15: Air India has cut fares by 20-46 per cent on certain flights on select domestic routes for travel up to September 18. Air India will charge an all-inclusive fare of Rs 2,729 on eight flights from Mumbai to Delhi and seven flights from Delhi to Mumbai till September 18. The fare on three flights from Delhi to Chennai and two flights from Chennai to Delhi would be Rs 3,079. On two flights from Calcutta to Mumbai, the all-inclusive fare would be Rs 3,529 for the period. Meanwhile, state-run oil firms today slashed jet fuel prices by 3.2 per cent in line with the softening international rates.                             
	 New Delhi, Sept. 15: Grupo Mexico has asked a US court to disallow rival bidder Sterlite from increasing the offer price for acquiring Asarco. On September 11, Sterlite had submitted an all-cash bid of $2.565 billion.                            
	 New Delhi, Sept. 15: Mumbai SEZ has sought extension, for the third time, for the validity of its in-principle approval granted by the government in 2006. The SEZ is promoted by Reliance Industries chairman Mukesh Ambani and his aide Anand Jain.                             
	 New Delhi, Sept. 15: The government has issued bonds worth over Rs 10,000 crore to three oil marketing PSUs to compensate them for the losses incurred on account of selling petroleum products below market price.                                                                                                                           
